Git Insight – Full Project Flow
OVERALL ARCHITECTURE
The system has three main layers:
1. Data Extraction Layer
2. Local Intelligence Layer
3. LLM Reasoning Layer
PHASE 1 – DATA EXTRACTION (Runs Once)
File: git_full_intelligence_extractor.py
This script:
- Runs git commands (log, branch, merges, diff, rev-list)
- Extracts commit, branch, merge, and divergence data
- Builds a structured JSON file: git_full_metadata.json
No LLM is used in this phase.
PHASE 2 – LOCAL INTELLIGENCE (Runs Per Question)
When a user enters a question:
1. load_full_data() reads git_full_metadata.json.
2. filter_commits() narrows commits based on:
- Contributor name
- Time phrases (last week, recent, etc.)
- Keywords
- Relevance scoring
3. build_structured_context() creates a repository summary:
- Total commits
- Branch metrics
- Merge metrics
- Divergence data
4. format_commits_for_llm() converts relevant commits into readable blocks.
All of this happens locally. No data is sent to the model yet.
PHASE 3 – LLM REASONING
Only after filtering and summarizing, the system sends:
- Repository summary
- Relevant commits only
- User question
The model never receives:
- Entire git history
- Raw JSON
- Source code
